1 Sec. 6. 32 MRSA §6100-Y, sub-§1, ¶F, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 662, §2, is
2 amended to read:
3 F. The authorized delegate engages in an unsafe or unsound practice.; or
4 Sec. 7. 32 MRSA §6100-Y, sub-§1, ¶G is enacted to read:
5 G. The authorized delegate violates the provisions of section 6100-L, subsection 3.
6 Sec. 8. 36 MRSA §5219-CCC is enacted to read:
7 §5219-CCC. Money transmission tax credit
8 For tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, a person is allowed a credit against
9 the tax otherwise due under this Part in an amount equal to the fee paid by the person to
10 send a money transmission under Title 32, section 6100-L, subsection 3, paragraph D.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This bill requires a sender of a money transmission to pay a remittance fee to be
1133 deposited into the General Fund. The sender is entitled to a state income tax credit in the
1144 amount of the fee if the sender files a state individual income tax return with either a valid
1155 social security number or a valid tax identification number.
